title: Australia puts off tour
text:
Source: Shanghai Daily | October 2, 2015, Friday | Print Edition 
Australia has postponed its cricket tour to Bangladesh because of concerns over player safety. 
Cricket Australia chief executive James Sutherland said yesterday the tour, scheduled to start with a warm-up match tomorrow, would not go ahead as planned after Australia’s Department of Foreign Affairs identified a serious security risk. Sutherland said he’ll negotiate with the Bangladesh Cricket Board regarding potential future dates. The Australians, scheduled to leave last Monday, were to play two tests — from October 9 in Chittagong and October 17 in Dhaka.
